data:
The BM GRAZ dataset introduced by Kainz et al., Medical Image Computing and Computer-Assisted Intervention – MICCAI,2015. It consists in 11 1200 * 1200 pixels regions of interest of healthy human bone marrow from 8 different patients where tissue had been stained with Hematoxylin and Eosin.


It has been used in cell counting algorithms in specific regions of interests within tissues. See e.g. Rubens et al. (in preparation).
